scroggin
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a mixture of dried fruit, chocolate, etc., eaten by trampers as a high energy snack. (trampers');  a mixture of dried fruit, chocolate, nuts, etc. carried by trampers as a high-energy snack [? SCRAN + HOG]
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1945 NCC Small, Les Cleveland, R. Mason (`orig Canterbury ?')
