Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 97
Edition:
Quote: <i>scroggin</i> trampers' lightweight sustaining tucker mix of raisins, sultanas, nuts, chocolate and boiled sweets; `scrog' is Scottish and Nort Northern English dialect for `stunted bushes', which may or may not have transmogrified into scroggin. <i>scroggin n. NZ & Austral.</i> mixture of dried fruit, nuts, etc., eaten as snack by trampers etc. [orig. unkn.]
